Package: amatrix.opencl
Type: Package
Title: OpenCL and CLBlast Backend for 'amatrix'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Bradley", "Buchsbaum", email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Cross-platform GPU backend for the 'amatrix' package using
    'OpenCL' with 'CLBlast' for dense float32 linear algebra. Both libraries
    are located at run time (never linked), so the package builds and installs
    on any platform, including Windows; when no OpenCL runtime or 'CLBlast'
    is present the backend reports itself unavailable and 'amatrix' falls
    back to CPU execution. See amatrix_install_clblast() for a guided
    'CLBlast' setup.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/bbuchsbaum/amatrix
BugReports: https://github.com/bbuchsbaum/amatrix/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    amatrix,
    methods,
    Matrix
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
SystemRequirements: OpenCL runtime (ships with GPU drivers; loaded at runtime,
    not required to build or install); CLBlast (optional, loaded at runtime for
    GPU BLAS and linear algebra; install with amatrix_install_clblast())
NeedsCompilation: yes
Config/testthat/edition: 3
